I guess you should take this as a sign ~😉 if she’s a fan of pancakes give this one a try 🥞✨ and guess what’s the perfect pair to go along with pancakes, coffee✨❤️ . to be honest tho, I feel like decorating it is the most important step I think y’all agree as well🤣 . Here is the easy recipe . 1. Mix 280g of warm milk along with 2 tsp of white vinegar and let it sit for ten mins. 2. Add in 2 tbsp of granulated sugar along with 40g of unsalted butter and 1/2 tsp of vanilla extract and stir. 3. Combine with the dry ingredients ( 180g of all purpose flour, 1 tsp baking powder, 1/2 tsp baking soda, 1/4 tsp of salt and mix but don’t over mix , it’s ok to have little lumps. 4. Grease your pan with butter and cook on medium heat on both sides for around 2 mins. 5. Top it off with a small block of butter and your favorite toppings ( mine are blueberries and straberries) I recommend bananas as well✨ and enjoy ❤️ .
